WEBVTT

00:05.396 --> 00:07.442
Previously on
So Help Me Todd...

00:07.572 --> 00:09.357
MARGARET:
It is nice to have
my whole family--

00:09.487 --> 00:10.619
almost whole--

00:10.749 --> 00:12.099
together at this time.

00:12.229 --> 00:13.187
Where's your invisible
husband Lawrence?

00:13.317 --> 00:15.319
He can't make it.
Again.

00:15.450 --> 00:16.799
And I would like to see him.

00:16.929 --> 00:18.975
His job is very important.

00:19.106 --> 00:21.934
He is the chief of staff
for the governor of Oregon.

00:23.284 --> 00:26.548
["Amado Mio"
by Pink Martini playing]

00:28.332 --> 00:33.816
♪ Amado... ♪

00:33.946 --> 00:35.731
Oh, I meant to tell you,
I have a meeting

00:35.861 --> 00:37.559
on Monday morning with that
young woman you referred to me.

00:37.689 --> 00:38.864
Oh, um, Chloe?

00:38.995 --> 00:40.649
Yes, the bank robbery victim.

00:40.779 --> 00:42.303
Bank robbery?This does not concern you

00:42.433 --> 00:43.826
at that end of the table,
thank you.

00:43.956 --> 00:45.523
So, how is she?
I mean, what's going on with...?

00:45.654 --> 00:48.352
The bank won't pay her
medical bills or her lost wages,

00:48.483 --> 00:50.311
so she wants to sue the bank.

00:50.441 --> 00:51.660
Wait, why wouldn't the bank pay?

00:51.790 --> 00:52.965
Your sister had a patient
in the ER.

00:53.096 --> 00:54.358
This was like nine months ago.

00:54.489 --> 00:55.620
A bank teller.

00:55.751 --> 00:56.795
She was injured
during a robbery.

00:56.926 --> 00:58.449
That's so exciting.Exciting?

00:58.580 --> 00:59.929
She was handcuffed to a vault

01:00.060 --> 01:01.496
from Saturday night
till Monday morning.

01:01.626 --> 01:02.932
And they found
her half dead,

01:03.063 --> 01:04.325
with hideous lacerations

01:04.455 --> 01:06.196
and a compound fracture
of her right wrist.

01:06.327 --> 01:08.329
That's exciting to you?Well, it's interesting.

01:08.459 --> 01:10.983
And you referred her to Mom?
This Cleo?

01:11.114 --> 01:12.289
Chloe.ALLISON: Yeah,

01:12.420 --> 01:14.248
because her parents--
who were so sweet--

01:14.378 --> 01:16.250
were very worried about
all the medical bills,

01:16.380 --> 01:17.512
and Chloe doesn't have
health insurance...

01:17.642 --> 01:19.383
How much did the bank robbers
get away with?

01:19.514 --> 01:21.342
Well, Todd, we are not solving
a bank robbery.

01:21.472 --> 01:22.734
$870,000.What?!

01:22.865 --> 01:24.910
Almost a mil.That's a lot of money.

01:25.041 --> 01:27.087
I read about
it in The Sentinel.Yeah, I cowrote that story.

01:27.217 --> 01:28.523
You did?

01:28.653 --> 01:30.046
And we're repping her?
This is a family affair.

01:30.177 --> 01:32.266
No. It's a workers' comp case.

01:32.396 --> 01:33.876
It's far too small for me.

01:34.006 --> 01:35.617
I'll oversee it,

01:35.747 --> 01:37.967
but I'm giving the day-to-day
to my associate Susan.

01:38.098 --> 01:39.229
Susan.
The one that got away.

01:39.360 --> 01:41.275
From Todd.Okay.

01:41.405 --> 01:43.668
Anyway, I don't have time
for this case

01:43.799 --> 01:45.975
because I'm so busy planning

01:46.106 --> 01:47.629
for Thursday.TODD:Thursday?

01:47.759 --> 01:49.587
What's Thursday?Thanksgiving.

01:49.718 --> 01:52.677
I'm ordering
a 12-pound bird,

01:52.808 --> 01:54.201
and I saw the most
adorable little

01:54.331 --> 01:56.464
chocolate turkeys
for Clem.

01:56.594 --> 01:57.900
Now, if everyone
gets here by noon,

01:58.030 --> 01:59.902
we can all watch
the parade together.Mom?

02:00.032 --> 02:01.469
Are you forgetting?

02:01.599 --> 02:03.949
We're not gonna be here
for Thanksgiving this year.

02:04.080 --> 02:05.342
We're spending Thanksgiving
with Chuck's parents.

02:05.473 --> 02:06.952
CHUCK: Right, because
of the pandemic,

02:07.083 --> 02:08.867
we haven't seen my folks for
Thanksgiving in three years.

02:08.998 --> 02:10.304
We're going to their cabin
on Mount Hood.

02:10.434 --> 02:12.219
All right, uh,

02:12.349 --> 02:14.699
but, Clem, your daddy Lawrence
will be here for Thanksgiving.

02:14.830 --> 02:16.919
I'll just order a smaller bird.

02:17.049 --> 02:19.269
That butcher on Capitol
Highway makes the...

02:21.184 --> 02:22.794
Chet?

02:22.925 --> 02:26.058
Lawrence willbe here
for Thanksgiving, won't he?

02:26.189 --> 02:29.018
Yeah, the governor is doing
her annual work retreat

02:29.149 --> 02:32.064
over the holidays this year,
and all employees...

02:32.195 --> 02:33.675
Oh, Lawrence has to work
on Thanksgiving.

02:33.805 --> 02:36.199
But you and Clem will be here.

02:36.330 --> 02:39.115
Actually,
we're flying to Philly.

02:39.246 --> 02:39.942
My mom and my sisters
haven't seen Clem

02:40.072 --> 02:41.726
for a long time, so...

02:41.857 --> 02:44.773
No one will be home
for Thanksgiving?

02:44.903 --> 02:46.470
Uh...

02:46.601 --> 02:47.863
I'll be here.

02:47.993 --> 02:48.907
We can have Thanksgiving,
the two of us.

02:49.038 --> 02:50.170
It'll be fine.

02:50.300 --> 02:52.346
ALLISON:
Mom, I know you're upset,

02:52.476 --> 02:53.782
but we're all here
right now, so...

02:53.912 --> 02:55.697
I mean, we...

02:57.481 --> 03:01.268
♪ Begin tonight... ♪

03:02.269 --> 03:04.009
[door slams]Chet, I thought

03:04.140 --> 03:05.794
that you were going to be here.I got to take Clem to Philly.

03:05.924 --> 03:06.795
I told her,
I did tell her...

03:06.925 --> 03:08.536
[overlapping chatter]

03:08.666 --> 03:11.016
Okay, just a reminder,
I will be home for Thanksgiving.

03:11.147 --> 03:13.541
Which is a Thursday.
This year.

03:13.671 --> 03:16.108
[thunder crashing]

03:16.239 --> 03:18.067
Fantastic.
Yeah.

03:18.198 --> 03:20.461
♪ Begin ♪

03:20.591 --> 03:24.856
♪ Tonight. ♪

03:24.987 --> 03:26.945
I just really thought

03:27.076 --> 03:29.209
my whole family
would be here this year.

03:30.297 --> 03:33.561
[chuckles]
It's funny, isn't it?

03:33.691 --> 03:36.041
We want so badly
for our kids to grow up

03:36.172 --> 03:37.565
and fly out of the nest.

03:37.695 --> 03:39.436
And...

03:39.567 --> 03:41.960
then we get mad when
they don't fly back.

03:43.310 --> 03:44.876
Hi, am I interrupting?

03:45.007 --> 03:46.226
I wanted to ask
about the Chloe

03:46.356 --> 03:48.097
bank robbery
workers' comp thing?

03:48.228 --> 03:50.012
Oh, she should be here soon.
I'll go get the file.

03:50.142 --> 03:51.883
Is there a timeline
on this case?

03:52.014 --> 03:53.320
It seems pretty
straightforward,

03:53.450 --> 03:55.104
but, uh, well,

03:55.235 --> 03:56.932
Peter and I are supposed to go
to Hawaii for Thanksgiving.

03:57.062 --> 03:59.456
How nice. Romantic.

03:59.587 --> 04:01.197
[chuckles]
There's no rush on this.

04:01.328 --> 04:02.590
It's a workers' comp,
open and shut.[chuckles softly]

04:02.720 --> 04:05.419
So, just the two of you?
Which island?

04:05.549 --> 04:06.942
Kauai.

04:07.072 --> 04:09.074
And no, not just the two of us.

04:09.205 --> 04:10.815
Both our families,
all of our siblings.

04:10.946 --> 04:11.990
We rented a big house.

04:12.121 --> 04:13.644
It's a... a lot.

04:13.775 --> 04:16.256
You'll all be together.

04:16.386 --> 04:17.735
[sighs, clears throat]

04:17.866 --> 04:20.651
Listen, why don't you take
the rest of week off?

04:20.782 --> 04:23.350
Go home, pack, have fun.

04:23.480 --> 04:25.656
I'm not cooking for
Thanksgiving this year,

04:25.787 --> 04:28.355
so I am glad to cover
this case for a few days.

04:28.485 --> 04:29.878
I hate being idle.

04:30.008 --> 04:32.141
Here you go.
Super.

04:34.361 --> 04:35.144
[Margaret exhales sharply]

04:35.275 --> 04:37.581
She'll be fine.
Okay.

04:37.712 --> 04:40.280
MARGARET:
Let's get started.

04:40.410 --> 04:43.848
It's just so unfair.

04:43.979 --> 04:45.372
Our sweet little Chloe.

04:45.502 --> 04:47.765
She, uh, may never be able
to use that hand again.

04:47.896 --> 04:49.550
Well, she wouldn't be
the first bank teller

04:49.680 --> 04:51.073
to be injured
in a robbery.

04:51.203 --> 04:53.293
May I ask why
it took you nine months

04:53.423 --> 04:54.468
to pursue this matter?

04:54.598 --> 04:56.644
Hell, we didn't know
we could pursue it.

04:56.774 --> 04:59.081
That-that lady doctor
at the hospital...This is her mother, Dan.

04:59.211 --> 05:00.648
Oh, right.

05:00.778 --> 05:01.823
Well, your daughter
all but guaranteed us

05:01.953 --> 05:04.260
we wouldn't be responsible
for Chloe's medical bills.

05:04.391 --> 05:05.653
But the bank never paid.

05:05.783 --> 05:07.742
If we threaten
a lawsuit, they will.

05:07.872 --> 05:09.831
Did you get a letter

05:09.961 --> 05:10.962
from the State?YVONNE:
Yes, of course.

05:11.093 --> 05:12.964
It's just...

05:13.095 --> 05:14.749
it's so confusing.

05:14.879 --> 05:16.620
Oh, it's just a formality.

05:16.751 --> 05:18.535
In an ER,

05:18.666 --> 05:19.971
whenever evidence of
a violent crime appears,

05:20.102 --> 05:21.451
the hospital is required

05:21.582 --> 05:23.061
to notify the proper
authorities.

05:23.192 --> 05:24.454
I'll take care of it.

05:24.585 --> 05:27.370
Now, Chloe, if this
did go to trial,

05:27.501 --> 05:29.111
would you be
willing to testify

05:29.241 --> 05:30.852
about what happened?

05:32.375 --> 05:34.072
You have such a pretty view.

05:35.552 --> 05:37.032
You should put it
on Insta.

05:37.162 --> 05:39.687
Oh, Instagram?
[laughs]

05:39.817 --> 05:43.255
I don't use that one, actually,
but my children certainly do.

05:43.386 --> 05:44.953
Um, Chloe,

05:45.083 --> 05:46.955
how have you been
spending your time

05:47.085 --> 05:48.870
since the robbery?

05:49.000 --> 05:50.959
Uh, she hasn't been working.

05:51.089 --> 05:52.830
She's been at home
with us, and...

05:52.961 --> 05:54.266
Clip-Clop.

05:54.397 --> 05:56.225
Clip-Clop?

05:56.356 --> 05:57.531
It's free through
the public library,

05:57.661 --> 05:59.184
a streamy service
for movies.

05:59.315 --> 06:00.882
Streamingservice, Mom.

06:01.012 --> 06:02.884
DAN:Um...

06:03.014 --> 06:04.494
she's on it all day.

06:04.625 --> 06:06.061
[exhales softly]

06:07.236 --> 06:08.368
Chloe?

06:08.498 --> 06:10.848
Would you testify?

06:13.895 --> 06:17.377
I don't want to do
anything to... hurt the bank.

06:17.507 --> 06:19.640
Hurt the bank?Chloe, you're the one
who got hurt.

06:19.770 --> 06:22.251
They have insurance and funds
for things like this.

06:22.382 --> 06:25.123
The bank will be fine.
And so will you.

06:25.254 --> 06:26.342
DAN:
Um...

06:26.473 --> 06:27.778
how long will this take?

06:27.909 --> 06:30.781
Oh, a few weeks, maybe a month.

06:30.912 --> 06:32.479
Will you all be in town
for the holiday?

06:32.609 --> 06:34.959
Oh, yes, of course.
We'll all be home together.

06:35.090 --> 06:36.396
It's Thanksgiving.

06:36.526 --> 06:39.007
♪ ♪

06:41.618 --> 06:43.315
So, will you be baking?

06:43.446 --> 06:45.492
Yeah, I, uh, I've
already started.

06:45.622 --> 06:46.536
Oh.

06:46.667 --> 06:48.233
The elevators are
right there...

06:48.364 --> 06:50.322
[conversation continues
indistinctly]

06:55.806 --> 06:57.373
MARGARET:
Clip-Clop?

06:57.504 --> 06:59.070
YVONNE:
It's free through
the public library,

06:59.201 --> 07:00.681
a streamy service for movies.

07:00.811 --> 07:03.118
CHLOE:
Streamingservice, Mom.

07:03.248 --> 07:05.337
DAN:
Um...

07:05.468 --> 07:07.514
Oh, hi.
Uh, Chloe?

07:08.906 --> 07:11.779
I-I forgot my jacket.

07:11.909 --> 07:15.043
Okay, well, uh, I'm Todd.

07:15.173 --> 07:17.349
Your lawyer Margaret Wright
is my mom.

07:18.873 --> 07:19.917
Todd.

07:20.048 --> 07:21.658
Wright.

07:21.789 --> 07:24.748
Uh, yeah, I...YVONNE:
Okay.

07:24.879 --> 07:26.489
You found your jacket,
Chloe, honey?

07:26.620 --> 07:27.490
Chloe?

07:27.621 --> 07:29.753
Here we go.

07:29.884 --> 07:30.841
You-you want a snack?

07:30.972 --> 07:32.321
CHLOE:
God, no!Whoa.

07:33.975 --> 07:35.411
YVONNE:
Are you hungry?

07:35.542 --> 07:37.282
CHLOE:
No, don't touch me.

07:37.413 --> 07:39.633
Can you leave me alone?Okay.

07:39.763 --> 07:42.462
Chloe.CHLOE:
You always do this, always.

07:42.592 --> 07:44.028
Don't touch me.

07:44.159 --> 07:46.553
[overlapping arguing]

07:47.597 --> 07:48.816
LYLE:
Here's what I found.

07:48.946 --> 07:50.208
In my preliminary research,

07:50.339 --> 07:51.819
it appears that
Portland First Bank

07:51.949 --> 07:53.603
has paid workers' comp
to numerous individuals

07:53.734 --> 07:55.605
over the years.So, why wouldn't
they pay it here?

07:55.736 --> 07:57.128
Maybe their investigation
into the robbery

07:57.259 --> 07:58.478
hasn't closed yet?

07:58.608 --> 08:00.044
Mom, there's something
seriously weird

08:00.175 --> 08:01.393
about that
bank robbery girl.

08:01.524 --> 08:04.266
Workers' comp girl, Todd.
Thank you, Lyle.

08:04.396 --> 08:06.268
Let me know
if anything else turns up.

08:06.398 --> 08:07.748
I called your brother.

08:07.878 --> 08:09.880
What?
What did he say?He didn't pick up.

08:10.011 --> 08:11.839
Obviously too busy gallivanting
around with the governor

08:11.969 --> 08:13.231
to speak to his mother.

08:13.362 --> 08:14.711
You'd think the governor
was his mother.

08:14.842 --> 08:17.018
I bet if her husband
disappeared to Iceland,

08:17.148 --> 08:19.150
Lawrence would be right there
by her side in a flash.

08:19.281 --> 08:20.717
Happy Thanksgiving, Bob.

08:20.848 --> 08:23.503
Well, as you say,
his job is very important.

08:23.633 --> 08:25.200
Well, my job is important.

08:25.330 --> 08:27.594
I'm busy, but I always
prioritize my family above work.

08:27.724 --> 08:29.465
What? Since when do you
prioritize your family...?

08:29.596 --> 08:31.423
Todd, don't startwith me.Why-why are you mad at me?

08:31.554 --> 08:34.426
I am not mad at you...Lawrence and Allison
are the deserters.

08:34.557 --> 08:36.037
I'm gonna be home
for Thanksgiving!

08:36.167 --> 08:39.431
But I... am not.
I'm going out.

08:39.562 --> 08:41.521
For Chinese food.
Or to a movie.

08:41.651 --> 08:44.698
Or for the deepest
of Swedish massages.

08:44.828 --> 08:47.527
Is that even gonna be
open on Thanksgiving?

08:48.832 --> 08:50.660
Thanksgiving is canceled.

08:52.096 --> 08:53.576
[slams door]

08:53.707 --> 08:55.317
MARGARET [over recording]:
If this did go to trial,

08:55.447 --> 08:57.449
would you be willing to
testify about what happened?

08:57.580 --> 08:59.451
CHLOE:
You have such a pretty view.

08:59.582 --> 09:01.889
You should put it on Insta...

09:02.019 --> 09:04.369
MARGARET:
Oh, Instagram? [laughs]

09:04.500 --> 09:05.588
[phone chimes]

09:05.719 --> 09:06.937
I don't use that one, actually,

09:07.068 --> 09:08.939
but my children certainly do.

09:09.070 --> 09:11.072
[continues indistinctly]

09:14.466 --> 09:16.381
I don't want to sue the bank

09:16.512 --> 09:17.992
because I robbed the bank.

09:18.122 --> 09:20.124
Oh, my God.

09:20.255 --> 09:22.126
MARGARET:
Good night, Shirley.Mom!

09:22.257 --> 09:25.303
Mom.Todd, I have to go.

09:25.434 --> 09:27.305
I have to go cancel
my turkey order in person...

09:27.436 --> 09:29.090
Look at this message
I just got.[sighs]

09:29.220 --> 09:30.961
Can't this wait
until tomorrow?

09:31.092 --> 09:32.528
CHLOE:
I don't want to sue the bank

09:32.659 --> 09:34.486
because I robbed the bank.

09:36.576 --> 09:38.403
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Going down.

09:38.534 --> 09:40.580
♪ ♪

09:48.588 --> 09:50.720
YVONNE [sobbing]:
No.

09:50.851 --> 09:52.330
This is so awful.Oh, yeah.

09:52.461 --> 09:54.463
So, on Instagram,

09:54.594 --> 09:57.335
Chloe slid into Todd's BMs...

09:57.466 --> 09:58.815
DMs.
DMs.

09:58.946 --> 10:01.383
...and claimed
to have robbed the bank.

10:01.513 --> 10:02.906
This is very concerning

10:03.037 --> 10:05.039
because we're just about
to file the case,

10:05.169 --> 10:06.736
and if she's making
statements like that...

10:06.867 --> 10:09.260
And the Instagram messages
came from your account.

10:09.391 --> 10:14.701
Well, we-we took her phone away,
so she-she must have found mine.

10:14.831 --> 10:18.008
You see, Chloe is...
[sobs]

10:18.139 --> 10:19.880
She's...
She's not well.

10:20.010 --> 10:22.012
She has serious PTSD
from the robbery,

10:22.143 --> 10:24.885
and we don't...She's always been fragile.

10:25.015 --> 10:27.975
Emotionally. Depressive.

10:28.105 --> 10:30.717
She's been on medication
since she was 12.

10:30.847 --> 10:33.850
Well, I'll need a full list
of those medications.

10:33.981 --> 10:35.112
DAN:
Yes, of course.

10:35.243 --> 10:36.592
YVONNE:
She's never left home.

10:36.723 --> 10:38.072
We tried to get her
to apply to college,

10:38.202 --> 10:40.683
move in with friends,
but she never would.

10:40.814 --> 10:42.554
DAN:
We thought this job
would be good for her,

10:42.685 --> 10:45.122
but now she's much worse.

10:45.253 --> 10:46.863
YVONNE:
She's been imagining things.

10:46.994 --> 10:48.909
MARGARET:
What sort of things?

10:49.039 --> 10:50.475
YVONNE:
Well, yesterday she told us

10:50.606 --> 10:53.043
that she was responsible for
a terrorist attack in France.

10:53.174 --> 10:54.436
We don't know
what to do.

10:54.566 --> 10:56.481
And her doctors, well...

10:56.612 --> 10:58.527
Where is Chloe
right now?Upstairs.

10:58.658 --> 10:59.789
Medicated and asleep.

10:59.920 --> 11:02.444
I just have to ask this.

11:02.574 --> 11:04.533
There's no way Chloe
didrob the bank, right?

11:04.664 --> 11:06.230
No. No, no.[chuckling]:
No.

11:06.361 --> 11:09.407
No, we-we already went through
all this with the police.

11:09.538 --> 11:13.020
Dan, get-- get those documents
that we had to put together.

11:15.196 --> 11:17.851
That's, uh, Chloe's
bank accounts,

11:17.981 --> 11:18.852
credit cards,
all of ours, too.

11:18.982 --> 11:20.375
Everything we gave
to the police.

11:20.505 --> 11:21.637
TODD:
Chloe.

11:21.768 --> 11:23.030
DAN: It just doesn't make sense.

11:23.160 --> 11:24.292
TODD: Clancy. Who's Clancy?

11:24.422 --> 11:26.294
If Chloe had robbed the bank,

11:26.424 --> 11:28.644
would we be in $42,000
in credit card debt?

11:28.775 --> 11:30.951
This is all too much.

11:31.081 --> 11:32.822
[sighs]
You don't know what it's like

11:32.953 --> 11:33.954
to have a troubled child.

11:34.084 --> 11:35.216
[clattering]Ow.

11:35.346 --> 11:36.870
[quietly]:Sorry.

11:37.000 --> 11:40.047
Maybe if we hadn't gone to
that Blazers game that night,

11:40.177 --> 11:41.875
I mean, if we could have
been there for her.

11:42.005 --> 11:44.921
Yeah, the, uh, night
of the robbery

11:45.052 --> 11:47.271
we got cheapie seats
for our anniversary.

11:47.402 --> 11:49.317
They put us
on the kiss cam.

11:49.447 --> 11:50.579
[both chuckling]

11:50.710 --> 11:52.059
[voice breaking]:
Please help us.

11:52.189 --> 11:54.452
I'll do everything I can
to help your family.

11:54.583 --> 11:56.411
Thank you.

11:56.541 --> 11:58.500
Thank you so much.

11:58.630 --> 12:01.851
TODD:
God, all these bank
statements they gave us.

12:01.982 --> 12:03.984
These people have no money.

12:05.159 --> 12:08.902
Oh, hey,
are you Clancy?

12:09.032 --> 12:11.034
Chloe's brother?

12:13.123 --> 12:14.995
Fixing the lawn mower.

12:18.738 --> 12:21.175
[door clanking]

12:22.480 --> 12:24.134
[knock at window]

12:30.880 --> 12:32.490
I thought
she was sleeping.

12:32.621 --> 12:35.363
Why wouldn't she come down
and speak to us?

12:35.493 --> 12:37.931
The whole thing
just seems really weird.

12:38.061 --> 12:40.324
I mean, what if Chloe
was involved?

12:40.455 --> 12:42.500
Todd, that poor woman
didn't rob anything.

12:42.631 --> 12:44.285
She's troubled
and depressed.

12:44.415 --> 12:45.677
And there's
something about her

12:45.808 --> 12:47.070
I just can't quite
put my finger on.

12:47.201 --> 12:48.768
And that brother didn't seem
suspicious to you?

12:48.898 --> 12:50.900
What? With all those
sharp tools?

12:51.031 --> 12:53.033
Can you rob a bank
with a lawn mower?

12:53.163 --> 12:54.774
Todd, we are not
solving a bank robbery.

12:54.904 --> 12:56.036
That's what the police do.

12:56.166 --> 12:57.777
We are representing
the victim

12:57.907 --> 13:00.170
in her lawsuit
against the bank.You know what?

13:00.301 --> 13:01.824
I should talk to
the police and the bank.

13:01.955 --> 13:03.521
I just spoke to the police

13:03.652 --> 13:05.349
and I got the bank's original
security camera footage.

13:05.480 --> 13:07.656
It's 39 hours of Chloe
handcuffed to the vault.

13:07.787 --> 13:09.353
Excellent work, Lyle.

13:09.484 --> 13:10.746
I'll need you to review it
and let me know what you learn.

13:10.877 --> 13:12.226
Perhaps Todd can do that?

13:12.356 --> 13:14.097
I've got scheduled time off
starting now

13:14.228 --> 13:15.664
and I'm joining
my sister's family

13:15.795 --> 13:17.013
in Cannon Beach
for Thanksgiving.Oh!

13:17.144 --> 13:19.059
Textbook has a sister.

13:19.189 --> 13:22.410
Oh, well,
enjoy your time.

13:22.540 --> 13:25.195
Todd, I need you to review
these 39 hours of footage.

13:25.326 --> 13:26.849
What? But that'll
take 39 hours.Yes.

13:26.980 --> 13:28.329
And I need
a full report.

13:28.459 --> 13:29.852
When we present
the papers to the bank,

13:29.983 --> 13:31.288
we need to show
how horrific

13:31.419 --> 13:32.681
this entire ordeal
has been for Chloe.

13:32.812 --> 13:35.162
I think my PI services...Your unlicensed
PI services.

13:35.292 --> 13:37.555
...are better deployed
out in the field.

13:37.686 --> 13:39.862
Far, far out in the field.

13:41.559 --> 13:43.083
[chuckles]

13:45.912 --> 13:47.783
What's going on?

13:47.914 --> 13:49.872
That poor family.

13:50.003 --> 13:52.875
Poor like
money poor or...?

13:53.006 --> 13:55.965
Even if there is something
weird about them...

13:57.271 --> 13:58.620
...they're together.

13:58.750 --> 14:00.448
They're staying together.

14:00.578 --> 14:02.363
Fighting for each other.Okay, I see where
this is going.

14:02.493 --> 14:05.366
If my children...Don't bring us into this.

14:05.496 --> 14:06.628
You're the one who
canceled Thanksgiving.

14:06.758 --> 14:08.543
You're like the Grinch,
but a month earlier.

14:08.673 --> 14:11.024
Chet is flying across the
country to be with his family.

14:11.154 --> 14:12.939
Susan is crossing an ocean.

14:13.069 --> 14:14.810
Even Lyle is off
with his sister.

14:14.941 --> 14:17.508
Meanwhile, your brother and
sister are MIA during a crisis.

14:17.639 --> 14:18.858
Crisis?

14:18.988 --> 14:20.860
What crisis?

14:20.990 --> 14:22.687
My husband
disappeared, Todd.

14:22.818 --> 14:24.385
It's my favorite holiday.

14:24.515 --> 14:26.561
And none of you
thought to include me

14:26.691 --> 14:28.215
or invite me anywhere.

14:28.345 --> 14:30.652
Okay, well, I'm really sorry,
but... that wasn't me.

14:30.782 --> 14:33.960
I got married twice.

14:34.090 --> 14:36.179
I had three children.

14:36.310 --> 14:38.834
I did everything right.

14:38.965 --> 14:40.836
Where is everybody?

14:40.967 --> 14:42.882
Where is my family?

14:43.012 --> 14:44.274
Well,

14:44.405 --> 14:46.015
maybe Aunt Patty
could come down.[sighs]

14:46.146 --> 14:47.669
I don't want Aunt Patty
to come down.

14:47.799 --> 14:50.759
Well, you know,
I'll still be here.

14:50.890 --> 14:52.239
And I appreciate that.

14:52.369 --> 14:55.851
But what about Lawrence?
Why does he avoid us?

14:55.982 --> 14:56.983
Uh, he's always been
like this.

14:57.113 --> 14:58.375
He's just a jerk.

14:58.506 --> 15:03.076
Todd, I want
my whole family together.

15:03.206 --> 15:04.860
All of us.
All of my children.

15:04.991 --> 15:06.993
For once.

15:13.956 --> 15:15.958
♪ ♪

15:24.880 --> 15:26.273
[quietly]:
Oh, my...

15:30.451 --> 15:31.887
[groans]

15:32.018 --> 15:34.063
[sighs]
This is awful.

15:34.194 --> 15:35.543
[call chiming]

15:35.673 --> 15:37.545
Oh, uh...

15:37.675 --> 15:38.981
Hey.

15:39.112 --> 15:40.809
Hey, man, how's it going?

15:40.940 --> 15:42.680
Uh, just hanging in there.

15:42.811 --> 15:44.552
You?Yeah, good, good, um...

15:44.682 --> 15:46.771
I was just checking in
on-on your mom.

15:46.902 --> 15:48.338
Is she still upset?

15:48.469 --> 15:50.166
Yeah, but it's fine.

15:50.297 --> 15:51.602
I mean, it's not,
but it will be.

15:51.733 --> 15:52.952
I think.

15:53.082 --> 15:54.692
You and Al having fun?

15:54.823 --> 15:55.911
Oh, yeah, she's just out
with my...Oh, get the ball!

15:56.042 --> 15:57.826
Dribble, dribble, dribble!

15:57.957 --> 16:00.437
Oh, hey, Chuck, that reminds me,
do you know the person

16:00.568 --> 16:02.265
who runs the kiss cam
at the Blazer games?

16:02.396 --> 16:03.919
Yeah, my man Tony.

16:04.050 --> 16:05.921
His office is across from mine
at the Blazers HQ.

16:06.052 --> 16:07.488
Why do you ask?

16:07.618 --> 16:09.490
Can you possibly find out
about the game on, um,

16:09.620 --> 16:11.622
February 12th from this year?

16:11.753 --> 16:13.146
Who was on the kiss cam
that night and whatever?

16:13.276 --> 16:14.712
Just wondering.

16:14.843 --> 16:17.454
Sure, happy to look into it.
I got you, bro.

16:17.585 --> 16:19.761
Okay, um,
give my love to your mom.

16:19.891 --> 16:21.981
Uh, okay, will do.

16:22.111 --> 16:23.025
Got to get back to my family.

16:23.156 --> 16:25.593
Bye.[call disconnect chime]

16:25.723 --> 16:27.595
[sighs deeply]

16:27.725 --> 16:29.162
Family.

16:38.649 --> 16:41.652
["Walking in the Sun"
by The Magic Shop playing]

16:43.828 --> 16:45.047
[whistling]

17:00.062 --> 17:02.064
♪ ♪

17:15.077 --> 17:16.861
Just a moment.

17:16.992 --> 17:18.602
Lawrence?

17:18.733 --> 17:20.430
Todd, what are you...?Are you dressed

17:20.561 --> 17:22.258
as a mouse?
No.

17:22.389 --> 17:23.738
You have whiskers.I'm a vole.

17:23.868 --> 17:25.174
Okay.
What are you doing?

17:25.305 --> 17:26.654
I was FaceTiming Clem
before bed.

17:26.784 --> 17:28.090
Why are you here?

17:28.221 --> 17:29.831
You dress up as a vole
to put Clem to bed?

17:29.961 --> 17:31.528
We're reading

17:31.659 --> 17:33.704
Mr. Vole, Lady Mole,
and the Itty Bitty Shrew.

17:33.835 --> 17:36.838
What do you want?It's about Mom.

17:36.968 --> 17:38.883
What about her?

17:39.014 --> 17:41.147
You have to come home
for Thanksgiving.I can't do that.

17:41.277 --> 17:42.626
The governor and I have...You know, it's really hard

17:42.757 --> 17:44.193
to take you seriously
with the mouse whiskers.

17:44.324 --> 17:45.629
They're volewhiskers.

17:45.760 --> 17:47.327
And I'm not coming home,
I have to work.

17:47.457 --> 17:49.633
Come on!
You're never around.

17:49.764 --> 17:52.158
Your husband and daughter
eat with us every week,

17:52.288 --> 17:53.376
Mom's husband disappeared,

17:53.507 --> 17:54.943
and you've never
even called her.

17:55.074 --> 17:56.118
I sent her a text message.

17:56.249 --> 17:57.076
You sent her
a thumbs-up emoji.

17:57.206 --> 17:58.338
My mobile phone
isn't cleared

17:58.468 --> 17:59.730
for civilian use
or personal materials.

17:59.861 --> 18:01.123
God, you are
like a robot.

18:01.254 --> 18:04.083
I'm a vole!
And the thumbs-up emoji

18:04.213 --> 18:05.736
was meant to convey
strength and support.

18:05.867 --> 18:07.564
What? What are you even
talking about?

18:07.695 --> 18:09.305
Are you a part
of this family or not?

18:09.436 --> 18:11.481
You can't go around avoiding
all of us forever, you know.

18:11.612 --> 18:13.744
[laughing]:
I just-- Oops.

18:13.875 --> 18:14.876
Oh.

18:15.006 --> 18:17.313
Todd, I...

18:19.010 --> 18:23.232
Are you two hanging out...
without me?

18:28.324 --> 18:29.934
ALLISON:
Todd, it's not a big deal.

18:30.065 --> 18:31.110
Chuck's parents

18:31.240 --> 18:32.720
are a half hour away,

18:32.850 --> 18:34.025
and I just came to see
Lawrence for the night.

18:34.156 --> 18:36.332
You guys get together.
Without me.

18:36.463 --> 18:37.899
[stammering]:
I mean... well, sort of.

18:38.029 --> 18:39.770
Yes, but it's not like...

18:39.901 --> 18:41.816
Okay, if you had been nearby,
we would have included you.

18:41.946 --> 18:43.339
No, you wouldn't.We wouldn't.

18:43.470 --> 18:45.559
Okay, I'm just saying
that different siblings

18:45.689 --> 18:46.995
have different relationships
with each other.

18:47.126 --> 18:48.605
And Lawrence and I--

18:48.736 --> 18:50.694
You have a relationship.
With him. He talks to you.

18:50.825 --> 18:52.305
He tells you things about
his life? Him? He does?

18:52.435 --> 18:54.698
Yes.I don't want
to talk to you.

18:54.829 --> 18:57.092
Why should I?

18:57.223 --> 18:58.963
You've got Mom wrapped around
your little finger.

18:59.094 --> 19:01.009
You two can hang out

19:01.140 --> 19:03.620
and get ice cream
all you want.Hang out and get ice cream?

19:03.751 --> 19:05.405
Is that what you think
Mom and I are doing?

19:05.535 --> 19:07.146
I don't care what you do.

19:07.276 --> 19:09.800
Now she's gotten you
a job as a janitor

19:09.931 --> 19:10.845
in her office?

19:10.975 --> 19:11.889
That's great.
Good for you.

19:12.020 --> 19:13.152
I'm not the janitor.

19:13.282 --> 19:14.762
Fine, whatever.
Office cleaner.

19:14.892 --> 19:17.678
You get Mom all to yourself,
just the way you like it.

19:18.896 --> 19:20.942
Lawrence feels like...Oh, Lawrence
feels things?

19:21.072 --> 19:22.291
Wow, is that
a software upgrade?

19:22.422 --> 19:26.687
Todd, Lawrence feels like
Mom prefers you.

19:26.817 --> 19:27.949
Like you are her favorite.

19:28.079 --> 19:29.777
What?I know, it's crazy.

19:29.907 --> 19:32.910
It's crazy, and talking
favoritism is stupid anyway

19:33.041 --> 19:34.303
because Mom
and my relationship

19:34.434 --> 19:35.870
is so much deeper
than her relationship

19:36.000 --> 19:38.133
with either of you.Uh, you're not
her favorite.

19:38.264 --> 19:39.352
I'm not saying I'm her...He's her favorite.

19:39.482 --> 19:42.137
I'm not the favorite.Yes, you are.

19:42.268 --> 19:43.921
She talks about you
constantly.

19:44.052 --> 19:45.706
"My son, the chief of staff
to the governor of Oregon,

19:45.836 --> 19:47.186
"blah-blah-blah,

19:47.316 --> 19:48.709
"why won't he
come home to me?

19:48.839 --> 19:50.580
Wah-wah-wah."Okay, she does say those things,

19:50.711 --> 19:52.191
but Mom and my relationship
is much closer

19:52.321 --> 19:53.540
and more...I don't care.

19:53.670 --> 19:55.585
I don't care about any of it.

19:55.716 --> 19:57.718
Chet and I have
our own family now

19:57.848 --> 19:59.676
and we're gonna love
our children equally.

19:59.807 --> 20:01.374
Equally?
You have one child.

20:01.504 --> 20:02.679
Yeah, and we're not gonna
ship her off to military school,

20:02.810 --> 20:04.290
like I was.Like was done to me.

20:04.420 --> 20:05.987
Mom and Dad thought I was dumb,

20:06.117 --> 20:07.510
I was never gonna be the doctor

20:07.641 --> 20:09.904
that they wanted...
so they sent me away.

20:10.034 --> 20:11.993
Ejected me from this family.

20:12.123 --> 20:14.561
So then they can make you the
perfect little princess doctor.

20:14.691 --> 20:15.953
"Perfect little
princess doctor"?

20:16.084 --> 20:17.390
Are you kidding me?

20:17.520 --> 20:19.000
And worship at
the altar of Todd.

20:19.130 --> 20:20.654
She doesn't worship me,
she hates me.

20:20.784 --> 20:22.351
[scoffs]She doesn't hate you.

20:22.482 --> 20:24.353
A lot of the time...Her entire life
is focused on you.

20:24.484 --> 20:26.747
You're a mess.
You're the problem child.

20:26.877 --> 20:28.401
She bends over
backwards to help you,

20:28.531 --> 20:30.577
to fix you, to save you.

20:30.707 --> 20:33.754
And now she's, she's got you
mopping floors in her office?

20:33.884 --> 20:35.495
Okay, where did this
mopping thing come from?Great.

20:35.625 --> 20:37.671
She'd do
anything for you.All she talks about is you.

20:37.801 --> 20:39.760
Allison and I could burn up
in a fire and she'd be like,

20:39.890 --> 20:41.979
"Well, I still have Lawrence."

20:42.110 --> 20:43.372
Um, I think if I died
in a fire,

20:43.503 --> 20:44.678
she would be a little bit
more upset...

20:44.808 --> 20:46.984
Okay, jump in.
Let's find out.I have to be up

20:47.115 --> 20:48.899
at 0500 hours to escort
the governor to...Oh, okay, big shot.

20:49.030 --> 20:51.032
"0500 hours, metric time,
governor of Oregon.

20:51.162 --> 20:52.207
I'm so important."

20:52.338 --> 20:54.383
[fire crackling]

20:58.213 --> 21:02.565
Someday I am going to be
the governor of Oregon.

21:02.696 --> 21:04.828
And the last thing I need
is my stupid brother

21:04.959 --> 21:06.265
getting in trouble
with the law again

21:06.395 --> 21:07.396
and embarrassing me
publicly.

21:08.919 --> 21:11.226
♪ ♪

21:17.188 --> 21:21.541
You are not closer
to Mom than...When is Mom's birthday?

21:22.977 --> 21:25.284
♪ ♪

21:27.373 --> 21:28.330
Okay.

21:31.855 --> 21:34.858
["Maps" by Quiet Arrows playing]

21:44.738 --> 21:46.696
♪ Underneath
your knuckles white ♪

21:46.827 --> 21:48.916
♪ Clenching hands
are creased with lines ♪

21:49.046 --> 21:53.007
♪ Though they tremble,
you are bold ♪

21:53.137 --> 21:55.444
♪ Seal the letters
that you write ♪

21:55.575 --> 21:57.316
♪ By the wind and candlelight ♪

21:57.446 --> 22:00.884
♪ Still your words
remain aglow ♪

22:01.015 --> 22:03.844
♪ Oh, turn your face
and lift your eyes ♪

22:03.974 --> 22:06.150
♪ To the patterns in the sky ♪

22:06.281 --> 22:10.372
♪ Navigate the years of old ♪

22:10.503 --> 22:12.374
♪ Understand that passing time ♪

22:12.505 --> 22:14.463
♪ Travels forward and behind ♪

22:14.594 --> 22:18.162
♪ Only moments can you hold ♪

22:18.989 --> 22:23.951
♪ Oh... ♪

22:24.081 --> 22:25.692
[sighs]

22:25.822 --> 22:27.563
I can't believe you're making
me sleep on the floor.

22:27.694 --> 22:30.218
Feel free
to drive home.

22:30.349 --> 22:31.828
Does he ever stop
complaining?

22:31.959 --> 22:33.700
Oh, said from the comfort
of an actual bed.

22:33.830 --> 22:36.267
Can I at least get a pillow?

22:39.009 --> 22:41.142
If I were you, I'd sleep
with one eye open tonight.

22:41.272 --> 22:42.622
If you even think
about putting my hand

22:42.752 --> 22:44.450
in a glass of warm water,
I will kill you.

22:44.580 --> 22:47.409
Stop it, both of you.
Just go to sleep.

22:54.938 --> 22:56.679
Hey.

22:56.810 --> 22:59.465
[quietly]: What's the latest
with that case?

22:59.595 --> 23:01.031
Chloe,
the bank robbery thing.

23:01.162 --> 23:02.729
Oh, it's a mess.

23:02.859 --> 23:05.253
Chloe is now claiming
that sherobbed the bank.

23:05.384 --> 23:06.863
What?
Yeah, it turns out

23:06.994 --> 23:08.822
she has some serious
mental health issues.

23:08.952 --> 23:10.650
She struggles with depression

23:10.780 --> 23:12.869
and has been heavily medicated
for, like, her whole life.

23:13.000 --> 23:13.957
Wait, what?
According to who?

23:14.088 --> 23:15.524
Her parents.

23:15.655 --> 23:17.265
Dan and what's her name?

23:17.396 --> 23:18.962
Yvonne.

23:19.093 --> 23:20.399
I can hear every word
you're whispering!

23:20.529 --> 23:22.879
Please go to
bed right now.

23:35.065 --> 23:37.416
[birds chirping]

23:37.546 --> 23:40.027
Lawrence, you really have to
come home for Thanksgiving.

23:40.157 --> 23:41.681
For Mom.No.

23:41.811 --> 23:43.073
You can't just
walk out of your family.

23:43.204 --> 23:44.597
She's not coming.

23:44.727 --> 23:46.468
I really can't this year.And I can't either.

23:46.599 --> 23:48.905
Mom will be fine.
She's always fine.

23:49.036 --> 23:50.037
No, she pretends
to be fine,

23:50.167 --> 23:51.342
but she's not.

23:51.473 --> 23:53.083
Neither of you were there

23:53.214 --> 23:55.259
when Harry disappeared,
but I was.

23:55.390 --> 23:57.392
CHUCK:
Hey, guys.

23:57.523 --> 23:58.785
ALLISON:
Hey, babe.

23:58.915 --> 24:01.091
I'm...
I'm sorry, okay?

24:01.222 --> 24:03.006
Chuck's family is also going
through something this year.

24:03.137 --> 24:04.704
So, happy...

24:05.748 --> 24:06.880
Happy Thanksgiving.

24:07.010 --> 24:08.795
[car door shuts]

24:08.925 --> 24:10.013
[exhales]

24:10.144 --> 24:11.580
ALLISON:
Bye.

24:17.847 --> 24:19.196
All right.

24:20.633 --> 24:22.112
Goodbye.

24:25.768 --> 24:26.769
Okay.

24:26.900 --> 24:28.945
Sounds great.

24:29.076 --> 24:30.425
Robot.

24:38.477 --> 24:40.653
Hey, so, uh...
I was wondering...

24:40.783 --> 24:42.089
Is it maybe time for us
to start thinking

24:42.219 --> 24:43.656
about having a...?You know,
what's really weird is,

24:43.786 --> 24:45.614
Todd was saying
last night that Chloe,

24:45.745 --> 24:47.311
that bank robbery woman...Yeah.

24:47.442 --> 24:50.140
...has been heavily
medicated her whole life.

24:50.271 --> 24:52.447
But I treated her
in the ER,

24:52.578 --> 24:55.537
and we're using all these
painkillers and stabilizers

24:55.668 --> 24:57.887
and I'm asking all the "Are you
on any medications" questions

24:58.018 --> 25:00.977
repeatedly,
and... she wasn't.

25:01.108 --> 25:02.239
Nothing.

25:02.370 --> 25:04.546
Unless she lied.

25:04.677 --> 25:08.202
And also she was remarkably
calm about the whole thing.

25:08.332 --> 25:09.551
Like, I would have
never thought

25:09.682 --> 25:12.162
serious mental
health problems.

25:12.293 --> 25:14.556
Yeah, Todd asked me
something about her, too.

25:14.687 --> 25:16.340
Really?
About her parents?

25:16.471 --> 25:17.254
Apparently, they were
at the stadium

25:17.385 --> 25:18.821
the night of the robbery

25:18.952 --> 25:19.953
and they popped up
on the kiss cam.

25:20.083 --> 25:21.563
He wanted me
to check that out.

25:22.956 --> 25:24.348
Huh.

